    Enclosing class:
    BitSpliterator
    public static final class BitSpliterator.Array
extends BitSpliterator
    Implementation of BitSpliterator used to stream all values within a specified integer array representing indices in an order appropriate to manipulate a BitSet in parallel. The contents of that specified arrays must be in ascending order; behavior is undefined otherwise.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Array

        public Array​(int[] items,
             int position,
             int end)
        Creates a BitSpliterator.Array with the specified starting and ending indices position and end. The values within the specified range of indices within the array items will be processed.
        Parameters:
        items - the array of indices to be processed.
        position - (inclusive) the first index to include.
        end - (exclusive) the index after the last index to include.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if items is null.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if position is greater than or equal to end.

      • Array

        public Array​(int[] items)
        Creates a BitSpliterator.Array covering the entirety of the specified array. The values within the specified array items will be processed.
        Parameters:
        items - the array of indices to be processed.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if items is null.
